result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica Rae Irish was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Court costs on Count 1 shall be paid from bond. Bond applied to court costs, court-appointed attorney fees and GAL fees in 22JC2 and 22JC3.
Court waives costs on remaining counts.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample. 
Defendant shall have such assessments, treatment, counseling and programming as DOC deems appropriate. 
Defendant shall not go upon the property of CM/DM in Bagley. Defendant may have contact with CM/DM but that contact shall occur only between the hours of 8am and 8pm. The defendant shall not engage in harassing conduct, the definition of harassment being that from Section 813.125(1)(am)(2). That being engaging in a course of conduct or repeatedly committing acts which harass or intimidate another person and which serve no legitimate purpose. The legitimate purpose here is to organize contact between defendant and her children.  And for the CM/DM to inquire about Ms. Irish's well-being.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jessica Rae Irish in court.  Attorney Lisa Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Ryan Kieler in court for Jessica Rae Irish. There is no agreement in this case. Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives rights. Defendant pleads no contest charges. Defendant and Attorney Kieler have short discussion. Court accepts plea and finds defendant guilty of charges. Court reviews rights lost due to felony conviction. State remains silent as to sentencing. Attorney Ryan Kieler heard on sentencing. Defendant heard. Court heard and orders 2 years probation for Ct 1 and 1 year probation for Ct 2 with the following conditions: Defendant shall not go upon the property of CM / DM in Bagley.  Defendant may have contact with CM/DM but that contact shall occur only between the hours of 8am and 8pm. The defendant shall not engage in harassing conduct, the definition of harassment being that from Section 813.125(1)(am)(2).  That being engaging in a course of conduct or repeatedly committing acts which harass or intimidate another person and which serve no legitimate purpose. The legitimate purpose here is to organize contact between defendant and her children and for the CM/DM to inquire about Ms. Irish's well-being; to have such assessment, treatment, counseling, and programming that DOC deems appropriate, to pay court costs on Ct 1 and waives costs on Ct 2, and to submit a DNA sample. If revoked, 4 days credit.
